caption.text: Day 3 #TwitchCon! The last day! Wow! What a FUN filled weekend and I learned so much at this conference 😁😁 Made so many new friends and witnessed a really amazing and super friendly community of gamers and live streamers. I can wait to create my #Twitch account and start live streaming 👏🏽👏🏽 Can’t wait for #Twitcon 2020 #sandiego #sdcc #california #gamers #videogames #maccosmetics #mua #fun

After finishing the new Link’s Awakening on Switch a couple nights ago I sat there truly feeling like I was 9 years old again reflecting on my journey once more... As if playing this game for the very first time and watching the story unfold you truly feel for every character here. You even understand this world’s monsters with their motives for keeping Link from waking in the final moments of defeat .
- 
After all these years this game still puts me in the feels. Such an amazing tiny tale packed  with so much charisma. From Marin to Tarin to even the Flute Kid found deep in the labrynth’s attempting to stop you in your tracks! Everyone has a purpose, a place and here we are re awakening this masterpiece 26 years later!
-
-
-
-
-
-
-
-

caption.text:
The two biggest mistakes I see Mercy players make are
1. Using Rez without checking position. There’s a difference between a risky rez and a rez that was always going to fail. 
2. Not preferring targets- a low dps comes before a half health tank. Keep an eye on your other healer. You can usually allow an off tank to die for the sake of your main (unless your zar is very charged or something). Flick your beam to characters who are frontlining or about to take damage.
I make plenty of these mistakes too, but being aware is the first step to getting better ☺️

caption.text: I gotta split this one into parts in the comments because insta won’t let me post all of it... Y’ALL DIDN’T SEE THIS COMIN DID YA! I know almost everyone finna disagree with me on this one so imma explain more so why Luke is #1 in my next post but this is all about Anakin. Anakin is basically the King of GA and CS having the best crowd control in the game, like it’s crazy he can wrack up kills in those modes like no problem, being the tank of the light side plus dishing out the same damage he’s a threat in those modes. In HvV it’s crazy lemme tell ya. But he’s just not the best in HvV or 1v1s, lemme tell you why. His stamina is definitely not the best and you seem run out faster than other heroes (his blocking is great tho), Anakin’s attacks are pretty easy to dodge if you see em coming. Anakin without a doubt has one of the best chain of abilities but since they got nerfed they don’t do as much damage anymore besides to infantry. DEADASS the only reason why Anakin’s are always on the leaderboard is just because of his abilities, Heroic might, pull dominance, and retribution gets you points easily. You can literally have 3 eliminations but still make top 5 just due to that. As a Kylo or Vader there’s no reason dying to an Anakin unless you’re getting gang banged by the opposing team or you’re game is lagging it’s ass off or when the games lightsaber combat was shit. Lets talk good stuff about him now yay! Anakin is easily one of the best heroes against blaster villains and palps just because of his pull. Should we get into abilities? Yes we should, they are: passionate strike, Heroic might, pull dominance, and retribution. Alright let’s begin with passionate strike, this is pretty much useless now unless you’re trying to get that last swing from a person constantly blocking, but this is one of the easiest to dodge to. Nothing much to say about it honestly. Next Heroic might which is definitely his highlight being able to do a large radius all around him. This THE best ability in GA/CS without a doubt just because of his circle range and being able to grow if you are getting damaged. Only thing that’s kinda meh is that most see it coming unless you get a chain.

This game is a truly hidden gem on the famicom.
Holy Diver.
Holy sh*t I should say. Irem outdid themselves with this one. The game probably didn’t make it to the US or EU because of its religious imagery. If you haven’t played it, go get a copy!!

caption.text:
Digital Devil Saga 1 - Beat: 17 November 2005 Time: 74:59
Digital Devil Saga 2 - Beat: 4 May 2006 Time: ??? Digital Devil Saga was the first MegaTen game I really delved into. I couldn't find a copy of Nocturne anywhere so this had to do. The bad thing about my copy was that the dudes at GameStop couldn't find the box it came with. C'est la vie. 
This game felt like a journey for me because I wasn't at all used to the way MegaTen games were played. Their obtuse mechanics and unique storytelling were totally new for me but those fall and winter months were about that journey. 
While waiting for the second game to come out, I played Dragon Quest VII and, wouldn't you know, it felt odd NOT having a devour option in the battle menu to eat your enemies! XD

I really appreciated the different tone and  music Digital Devil Saga 2 provided. It didn't take me as long to finish it and I don't remember much of it. But that opening stage after the end of the first game was pure class.

Afro Samurai🎮
*
*De quien?: Bandai Namco
*Cuando salio?: Enero 2009
*Que onda?: Aventura, beat em'up
*
*Análisis de Orina
*
*Un samurai que es afro, que fuma y que tiene una katana con la cuál descuartiza a cuanto enemigo se le acerqué dejando grandes charcos de sangre... No puede fallar!... Puta madre!!! SHUT UP AND TAKE MY MONEY....MMM...No campeón... Disculpa, pero no. Siempre hay un "BUT" y éste es uno MUY grande.
*Basado en el manga de Takashi Okashi y posteriormente un anime producido por el mismisimo Samuel L. Jackson. Afro samurai nos cuenta la historia de nuestro amiguero Afro a quien le asesinaron a su padre y decide buscar VENGANZA en esta vida o en la que viene... A no, para!, eso era de una peli?...
*El juego tiene un estilo grafico animado muy bien logrado y pintoresco. La bandas de hip-hop la verdad que le aportan mucho al juego por mas que no sean de mi estilo de musica favorito. La jugabilidad es bastante intuitiva.
*Ahora arrancan los BUT😧... Es muy pero muy repetitivo, se vuelve todo el tiempo lo mismo. El sistema de combate termina siendo un "machaca botones" a lo bobo, los pocos puzzles que tiene... Ni se si llamarlos puzzles.
Loco! Posta que le puse onda al juego y me llamaba mucho la atención, puede ser que yo le puse la vara muy alta y no cumplio ni de cerca. Fueron casi 10 horitas (seee 10 Fucking horas) que para ser un juego no es mucho, pero se me termino haciendo mucho mas largo que otros de 15hs.
*
*Lo ATR:
+Graficos
+Voz de Samuel L. Jackson
+Mas sangre que peli de Tarantino.
*
*Corta la Mecha:
-repetitivo a cagarse
-puzzles facilones
-A veces la camara es el peor de los enemigos.
*
*Puntaje: 6,5
*
*

caption.text:
Super Mario Kart
1992
.
Would you believe I just added this to my collection today. Well, I did have this game as a kid and believe me it got played a ton! Many, many nights were spent staying up super late with friends having some of the best times.
.
Although it’s an absolute classic, launched one of the best racing game series to this day, but this one definitely feels like 1992. Another reason why it took me so long to pick this up, is folks want a fortune for it, luckily I got it cheap and it has a great home up on the SNES shelf for many years to come.
.

caption.text:
My heart started racing when he mentioned the horses. I knew she would say something. That horse means everything to her.
"Well what do we have here," he said smugly.  He motioned for one of his men to grab her from the line. I tried to hold on to her but Kitchi held me back. "I said what DO WE HAVE HERE!?" His tone grew more annoyed. 
He stepped closer and blows his cigar in her face.
"Look you don't appear to be like these savages here but I can't quite put a finger on what the hell you are. Let's try again. I'll go first, you seem to be the slow type.
I'm General James Steel and you are?"
She mumbled, "I'm Jolene and that's my horse."
"I'm sorry would you kindly speak up!" He motioned for his man to strike her.
The soilder grabbed her by the back of her hair and pulled.
"You heard the General, speak up!"
"Ouch, I said my name is Jolene and that's my horse!"
The General laughed. "Well, look at you thinking women can actually own anything. Look I thought you was a boy and was about to enlist you in the greatest army in the world but now you can shut your mouth and get back in line!"
The soldier pushed her back in line while another brought out our horse's. "Found two more out back sir."
"Figured as much they don't know how to tell the truth," the General sneered. 
He walked up to my Enisi and glared at her. "You said you only have two horse's,  what did I say about doing anything stupid?"
There is no lie we only own two horse's the other two belong to these men."
He puffed out his chest "Whatcha doing with the slow kid?"
"She's with us and that's all you need to know Sir."
"Hmph I'm getting tired of being disrespected. I think it's about time y'all learned a hard lesson." He grins wickedly as he pulls out his revolver and cocks it. "You all are gonna learn!"

Well it's not the most professional comparison but here's an idea of the difference between normal mode with the Super 64 and Slick Mode. I still want to try this on the plasma screen TV to see if it looks better because in general this TV isn''t so hot. But I'm actually surprised at the Slick Mode feature. Rather than it making everything blur together it seems subtle enough to make the naturally blurry N64 textures seem unaffected while cleaning up the pixelated artifacting around some of the blown-up imagery. Although the test pattern colored bars when your game doesn't boot certainly concerned me at first and I notice that you'll lose the first few seconds of the booting screen  whole it transmits the signal. It's not major but... it's something to note.
.
It certainly is doing better than this cheap third party controller I'm testing out too. The thing barely fits in the controller port, the stick seems to always be pulling in a different direction as soon as I let go, and the buttons, while enjoyably clicky, are a bit too deep and thus require more pressure to push with the proper timing.
.

caption.text:
La primera vez que fuimos ahí tenía 15 años, es la primera vez que recuerdo haber estado ahí. Fue catastrófico: terminé hablándole con violencia a alguien que amenazaba la paz de mi primer amor, jaja justo a mi me iba a pelear?! De haber sabido que era de una de las familias más peligrosas de ese entonces quizás hubiese sido distinto, no lo sé, pero si una cosa supe siempre es que no dejaría que nadie dañe a alguien que quiero. 
Las siguientes veces no las recuerdo, pero la ante última sí, fui empleada, mi primer trabajo. Ahí tuve que sacar a la luz simpatía, responsabilidad, frialdad, y más violencia. Terminé peleando con un chico, dos veces, y la última gané yo, no por fuerza, sino que él estaba tan drogado (y por ahí no tanto, porque hasta planeó ir con alguien para afanarme) que no podía ni iba responder luego de que le removí la mandíbula de un derechazo. 
Y de las últimas fueron visitando amigas que hice ahí. Siempre un mate, y un poco de metegol o pool para no perder la costumbre. 
Los videos fueron: piñas, besos, mates, amistad, primer trabajo, complicidades, baño público, mucha droga (no mía), pff... Las paredes de Satanás eran las que guardaban mucho, no sólo por los escupitajos ni las huellas de zapatillas, sino porque también eran testigo y refugio  de todos los chicos y grandes que iban a despejarse un ratito y no morir en el intento.

Poesia de um Gamer...
.
Sentado no velho sofá da sala ou
a na velha cadeira Tramontina
até mesmo jogado no chão
para começar mais uma jogatina.
.
As vezes em pé na frente a tela
no cantinho vou esquivando
retorcendo o pescoço todo
quando passam frente dela.
.
Em casa parece que ninguém sabe
o significado de partidas online
mas por aviso é que não falta
que jogo online não se pausa.
.
As visitas já sabem as regras
és o P2 e senta a direita
e não me deixe cair controle
senão em casa tu nunca mais entra.
.
Escolhe aí o teu personagem,
o pelotão ou time mais forte
depois não quero choro de noob
dizendo que isso foi jogo de sorte.
.
Nem vêm com macetes do youtube
seja gamer e venha na raça
disputa com o que sabes
porque o jogo tem tutorial ''disgraça!''
.
Entre Camper, Griefer, Hacker
e Lags do dia a dia
vou eu aqui levando.
.
Entre You lose, Game over,
The and, Wasted e
Kills que a vida me dá
vou eu aqui elevando.
.
Procurando Glitchings,
Eeaster eggs e defeitos,
a conquista e platina sonhada
o golpe perfeito.
.
Jogar não é só uma opção
é amor, é estilo de vida
é mais que cores na sua tv
isso é tecnologia.
.
E assim vai terminando essa poesia
meu tempo vai acabar agora
o cara da locadora já vêm vindo
pra perguntar quer mais uma hora?
.
Washington Anjos
.
.
.
.

One of last years’ best that I have recently replayed, I thought I may as well review God of War given it’s probably one of the best games of all time. While Red Dead Redemption 2 was unlucky not to win the top prize at the 2018 Game Awards, God of War was a very deserving winner.

While there is a huge tonal shift away from the original God of War games, it still holds on to what made them so good. The gameplay still feels more or less the same, but the story has really matured.

While there was always something happening or something to kill in the older games on the series, God of War isn’t afraid to stop every now and then to reflect and bask in the beauty of the Norse world.

Persona 3 – Beat: 11 November 2007 Time: 129: 30
Persona 3 – The Journey – Beat: 5 November 2010 Time: 64: 11

I remember the summer of 2007. There was no expectation for another release from Atlus. I was already acquainted with the world of Persona and MegaTen, so at that point only Atlus fans and the odd weirdo were looking forward to this. 
I had pre-ordered it at GameStop and they didn't get it until Thursday of release week (Games and movies were released on Tuesdays). I played it for a few months and those blue screens and menus and music blended with the long hazy days of late summer, the chilly nights of mid autumn, and the frozen reverberations of winter chill. 
I still have mixed feelings about this game. But is it a good game? Yup! I'd play the PSP port in a heartbeat if I find a reasonable priced copy.
